WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:02.830
♪♪

00:04.210 --> 00:05.120
Bex:
 Previously, on Andi Mack...

00:05.120 --> 00:06.580
I need to talk to you.

00:06.580 --> 00:07.750
-Okay.
-Andi--

00:07.750 --> 00:09.750
-Andi!
-Who's that?

00:09.750 --> 00:12.210
It doesn't matter.
What were you gonna say?

00:12.210 --> 00:13.250
I'll tell you later.

00:13.250 --> 00:15.540
Look at you guys.
Here, together.

00:15.540 --> 00:18.380
We're getting a birthday present
for Amber.

00:18.380 --> 00:20.250
You remember her,
right, Bex?

00:20.250 --> 00:23.750
Jonah's girlfriend
who's still his... girlfriend.

00:23.750 --> 00:25.790
See how this
makes her eyes sparkle?

00:25.790 --> 00:28.210
Wow. You look
really pretty.

00:28.210 --> 00:29.420
Thanks.

00:29.420 --> 00:32.420
That one likes you even if
he doesn't know it yet.

00:32.420 --> 00:33.620
You don't know that.

00:33.620 --> 00:35.120
You'll see.

00:35.120 --> 00:38.580
Thanks, Andi.
You're a great... pal.

00:43.380 --> 00:45.540
Guys, I need a face
for picture day.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.250
-Too easy.
-(Andi laughs)

00:48.250 --> 00:49.920
Listen, this is important.

00:49.920 --> 00:52.420
In grade school,
I went with the classic,

00:52.420 --> 00:53.580
"Please love me."

00:53.580 --> 00:56.330
But this is middle school.
I want to branch out.

00:56.330 --> 00:57.580
Show some moxie.

00:57.580 --> 00:59.420
Which one of these
do you like better?

01:00.500 --> 01:02.250
"Young Ben Affleck"?

01:03.670 --> 01:06.210
Or...

01:06.210 --> 01:08.420
"Future yogurt millionaire."

01:08.420 --> 01:11.330
You do know
picture day's a racket?

01:11.330 --> 01:14.880
Picture day
is a sacred institution.

01:14.880 --> 01:17.040
You can get an eight by 10
picture of yourself

01:17.040 --> 01:20.380
from any photo lab in the
country, for two dollars.

01:20.380 --> 01:24.080
It's not just any
eight by 10 picture of me.

01:24.080 --> 01:27.380
It's an eight by 10 picture of
me perched awkwardly on a stool,

01:27.380 --> 01:29.790
in front
of a blue backdrop.

01:30.830 --> 01:33.120
Ease up.
I think you hit a vein.

01:37.380 --> 01:39.880
Excuse me. Just wanted
to introduce myself.

01:39.880 --> 01:42.460
I'm the new principal,
Dr. Metcalf.

01:42.460 --> 01:45.420
Nice to meet you.
Andi, Cyrus, Buffy.

01:45.420 --> 01:48.920
I want you to know, I'm not a scary
principal, I'm an approachable one.

01:48.920 --> 01:51.330
I don't see any reason
why we can't be friends.

01:51.330 --> 01:54.380
(sniffs)
Well, I do see one reason.

01:54.380 --> 01:56.790
-Me?
-Your attire.

01:56.790 --> 01:58.790
Specifically, your leggings.

02:02.250 --> 02:04.540
When was the last time you read the
Jefferson Middle School dress code?

02:04.540 --> 02:06.460
I didn't know there was one.

02:06.460 --> 02:09.330
Of course there's a dress code.
You're here to learn,

02:09.330 --> 02:11.920
not distract each other
with your body parts.

02:11.920 --> 02:14.750
Who am I distracting?

02:14.750 --> 02:16.540
Because that would be a first.

02:16.540 --> 02:18.620
I want you to know,
I have a sense of humor,

02:18.620 --> 02:21.540
but I'm choosing
not to exercise it right now.

02:21.540 --> 02:24.380
I hear if you don't
exercise a sense of humor,

02:24.380 --> 02:26.540
it loses muscle tone.

02:26.540 --> 02:27.540
(laughing)

02:29.960 --> 02:31.290
Nothing?

02:31.290 --> 02:33.250
Tough crowd.

02:33.250 --> 02:35.420
This went south very fast.

02:35.420 --> 02:38.790
I will be distributing a copy of
the dress code to every student.

02:38.790 --> 02:41.830
You can plead ignorance
today but not tomorrow.

02:41.830 --> 02:44.120
Which is picture day!
Don't forget!

02:44.120 --> 02:46.420
No chance of that!

02:46.420 --> 02:50.210
Sorry, that was an involuntary
response to the words "picture day."

02:55.420 --> 02:56.960
(theme music playing)

02:56.960 --> 03:00.080
♪ I'm standing on the edge ♪

03:00.080 --> 03:03.080
♪ And everything I know-oh-oh ♪

03:03.080 --> 03:04.710
♪ Has blown away ♪

03:06.290 --> 03:09.540
♪ Life is upside down ♪

03:09.540 --> 03:12.380
♪ But any way it go-o-oes ♪

03:12.380 --> 03:14.250
♪ I'll work it out ♪

03:15.620 --> 03:19.330
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh ♪

03:19.330 --> 03:21.380
♪ Here we go ♪

03:22.880 --> 03:24.000
♪ One, two, three! ♪

03:24.000 --> 03:26.120
♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

03:26.120 --> 03:28.580
♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪

03:28.580 --> 03:30.500
♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪

03:30.500 --> 03:33.000
♪ But I'm with you all the way ♪

03:33.000 --> 03:35.540
♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

03:35.540 --> 03:37.960
♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪

03:37.960 --> 03:40.330
♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪

03:40.330 --> 03:43.210
♪ But I'm with you all the way ♪

03:43.210 --> 03:44.670
♪ All the way ♪

03:46.460 --> 03:48.420
"No jerseys, no tank tops,

03:48.420 --> 03:49.460
no crop tops"?

03:49.460 --> 03:52.500
"No shorts, no leggings,
no yoga pants."

03:52.500 --> 03:54.420
"No oversized clothing."

03:54.420 --> 03:55.670
You're making
that up.

03:57.330 --> 04:00.290
"No oversized clothing"?

04:00.290 --> 04:03.580
Why would anyone
ban oversized clothing?

04:03.580 --> 04:05.620
Is he against being cozy?

04:05.620 --> 04:07.750
So what are you gonna
do about it?

04:07.750 --> 04:10.750
Do? It's the dress code.

04:10.750 --> 04:14.830
It's a code. It's a school law!

04:14.830 --> 04:17.750
That's been in effect
since... February.

04:17.750 --> 04:21.209
It's not like he can monitor
what every student's wearing.

04:21.209 --> 04:23.830
He's definitely gonna
be monitoring Andi.

04:23.830 --> 04:27.290
And it's so unfair.
You're not a troublemaker.

04:27.290 --> 04:28.960
Maybe you should be.

04:28.960 --> 04:30.330
Cyrus:
No, no, no, no, no, no.

04:30.330 --> 04:32.790
You do not want to run
with the troublemakers.

04:32.790 --> 04:34.670
They're like coyotes.
They're mean,

04:34.670 --> 04:37.460
and they hunt in packs,
and they're night feeders!

04:37.460 --> 04:39.880
How's middle school
going for you, Cyrus?

04:39.880 --> 04:41.250
Bit of a roller coaster.

04:41.250 --> 04:43.380
Okay, well, there are
other kinds of troublemakers.

04:43.380 --> 04:45.580
Like the ones who don't
let somebody tell you

04:45.580 --> 04:47.620
what you can
and cannot wear.

04:47.620 --> 04:50.170
Does any of this
seem fair to you?

04:50.170 --> 04:52.170
-No.
-It's not fair.

04:53.500 --> 04:55.000
It's like we're in prison.

04:55.000 --> 04:57.170
Prison.

05:02.290 --> 05:05.540
♪ ♪

05:13.500 --> 05:16.250
♪ I come alive,
 one request tonight ♪

05:16.250 --> 05:19.250
♪ I'm comin' strong, game on,
 and I'm ready to fight ♪

05:19.250 --> 05:23.040
♪ I got the moves, so what you
gonna give me and my girls ♪

05:23.040 --> 05:25.500
♪ Hey, world,
 we're comin' for you ♪

05:25.500 --> 05:28.290
♪ Because my mind gets jumpin'
 and I won't be stoppin'

05:28.290 --> 05:31.080
♪ Just 'cause you've
 got somethin' to say ♪

05:31.080 --> 05:34.040
♪ Say it! Yeah, come on,
 come on, come on, say it! ♪

05:34.040 --> 05:37.250
♪ Yeah, come on, say it! Yeah!
 Come on, come on, say it! ♪

05:37.250 --> 05:40.250
♪ You know it makes me
 want it more ♪

05:41.330 --> 05:42.830
♪ Say it! ♪

05:42.830 --> 05:46.380
So... I gather you're not
happy with the dress code.

05:46.380 --> 05:49.960
Up until yesterday, we
didn't even know we had one.

05:49.960 --> 05:52.290
And everything
worked just fine.

05:52.290 --> 05:53.830
Did it?

05:53.830 --> 05:56.000
Then why am I here?

05:56.000 --> 05:58.750
Why does Jefferson Middle School
suddenly have a new principal?

06:03.380 --> 06:04.790
We give up!

06:04.790 --> 06:06.120
Your grade point averages.

06:06.120 --> 06:07.500
Your test scores.

06:07.500 --> 06:09.330
Your numbers are falling!

06:09.330 --> 06:13.540
This used to be the third-ranked
middle school in the city.

06:13.540 --> 06:15.040
Now it's 10th.

06:15.040 --> 06:17.330
Out of how many schools?

06:17.330 --> 06:19.000
A hundred and sixty-two.

06:19.000 --> 06:22.250
So that's what,
a 4.3 percent drop?

06:22.250 --> 06:25.330
Her test scores
are still very high,

06:25.330 --> 06:27.670
but her socks
may be too colorful.

06:27.670 --> 06:28.750
Oh!

06:28.750 --> 06:30.460
Oh!

06:31.500 --> 06:34.380
Still not exercising
that sense of humor, I see.

06:34.380 --> 06:37.000
We understand that there needs
to be a dress code.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.420
All we're asking
is that it's reasonable.

06:39.420 --> 06:41.330
Is that too much to ask?

06:42.920 --> 06:46.790
No, really, I'm asking.
This is my first protest.

06:46.790 --> 06:48.250
No, you're doing great.

06:49.620 --> 06:52.290
But this prison garb
is against dress code.

06:52.290 --> 06:54.420
-Since when?
-Since just now!

06:54.420 --> 06:57.460
-You can't do that!
-Oh, but I can.

06:57.460 --> 07:00.830
It's in another pamphlet
called, "Oh, But I Can!"

07:00.830 --> 07:02.330
(laughs)

07:03.420 --> 07:05.620
Consider my sense
of humor exercised.

07:06.880 --> 07:09.000
I liked it better
before he was funny.

07:11.540 --> 07:17.330
And now... you can either
go home and change,

07:17.330 --> 07:19.330
or just stay home,
until you decide

07:19.330 --> 07:22.420
that your education is more
important than your wardrobe.

07:22.420 --> 07:27.290
You'd suspend us just
for what we're wearing?

07:27.290 --> 07:30.540
Guys, come on. You've had your
fun, now let me do my job.

07:30.540 --> 07:32.330
I'm your principal,
not your prison warden.

07:33.920 --> 07:37.330
Students (chanting): Freedom of dress!
Freedom of dress!

07:37.330 --> 07:40.880
Freedom of dress!
Freedom of dress!

07:40.880 --> 07:44.500
X-X-L!
X-X-L!

07:44.500 --> 07:48.080
X-X-L!
X-X-L!

07:48.080 --> 07:49.920
X-X-L!

07:49.920 --> 07:53.540
Freedom of dress!
Freedom of dress!

07:53.540 --> 07:55.380
Freedom of dress!

07:59.120 --> 08:02.380
Freedom of dress!
Freedom of dress!

08:02.380 --> 08:06.000
Freedom of dress!
Freedom of dress!

08:06.000 --> 08:08.580
-Andi: What do we want?
-Students: Leggings!

08:08.580 --> 08:10.080
When do we want them?

08:10.080 --> 08:11.380
Students:
Now!

08:11.380 --> 08:13.420
And extra large sweatshirts!

08:13.420 --> 08:15.250
X-X-L!

08:15.250 --> 08:18.620
Students: X-X-L! X-X-L!

08:18.620 --> 08:21.670
X-X-L!
X-X-L!

08:21.670 --> 08:26.380
So, are you gonna suspend
all of these kids?

08:26.380 --> 08:30.170
Ooh, that's not gonna help this
school's academic standing.

08:33.289 --> 08:36.750
This is hilarious!
You know what's going on?

08:36.750 --> 08:39.960
Yeah, we're protesting
the dress code.

08:39.960 --> 08:41.039
Why?

08:41.039 --> 08:43.330
Because I wore leggings
to school yesterday,

08:43.330 --> 08:45.040
and I got in trouble for it.

08:45.040 --> 08:46.540
Can you believe that?

08:46.540 --> 08:47.790
Huh?

08:47.790 --> 08:51.420
I mean, the dress code's
totally unfair.

08:51.420 --> 08:55.420
They have all these random
restrictions, especially for girls.

08:55.420 --> 08:56.460
Oh.

08:56.460 --> 09:00.290
So it's like
we're in prison.

09:00.290 --> 09:02.420
Oh, I get it.
Like a metaphor.

09:02.420 --> 09:03.790
Exactly!

09:03.790 --> 09:06.960
So now we have this protest
that I'm the leader of.

09:06.960 --> 09:08.460
Do you wanna join us?

09:08.460 --> 09:11.380
I could totally get you
a uniform.

09:11.380 --> 09:13.830
Nah, I'm-- I'm good.

09:13.830 --> 09:15.790
Oh.

09:15.790 --> 09:18.290
-Okay.
-Hey, don't forget.

09:18.290 --> 09:20.710
Space Otters team picture's
this afternoon.

09:20.710 --> 09:23.290
First one ever, it's gonna
be in the yearbook.

09:23.290 --> 09:24.830
Exciting.

09:24.830 --> 09:26.750
You'll be there, right?

09:28.330 --> 09:32.420
Definitely. Yeah. If I can,
there's just a lot going on.

09:32.420 --> 09:34.080
No, listen,
you have to be there.

09:34.080 --> 09:35.330
This is important to me.

09:35.330 --> 09:37.790
I want the whole team
to be in this picture.

09:37.790 --> 09:39.750
Then I'll be there.

09:39.750 --> 09:42.920
You rock, Andiman.
You never let me down.

09:44.380 --> 09:47.210
Is he gonna
put on a uniform?

09:47.210 --> 09:49.120
Nah, he's good.

09:50.460 --> 09:52.670
He'd be better
if he put on a uniform.

09:54.580 --> 09:56.500
Bex:
My principle, okay?

09:56.500 --> 09:59.580
Yeah, that's right, it's
your body, your clothes,

09:59.580 --> 10:00.880
your style.

10:00.880 --> 10:02.880
There you go. Thank you
for joining the cause.

10:02.880 --> 10:04.170
Here you are.

10:04.170 --> 10:07.420
-Thank you for joining the
cause-- -I'm the principal here.

10:07.420 --> 10:09.500
Oh!

10:09.500 --> 10:11.380
Thank you
for joining the cause!

10:11.380 --> 10:14.330
Leave the premises immediately
or I will call the police.

10:14.330 --> 10:16.380
No need.

10:16.380 --> 10:18.120
I'll go.

10:18.120 --> 10:21.580
And I'm confiscating
this... box.

10:21.580 --> 10:23.000
All yours.

10:23.000 --> 10:26.040
♪ ♪

10:26.040 --> 10:28.750
♪ You can strive
 you can all show 'em ♪

10:28.750 --> 10:33.380
♪ Not try to prove
 you're a bigger man ♪

10:33.380 --> 10:35.000
-(students cheering)
 -♪ Don't stop ♪

10:35.000 --> 10:37.380
♪ Jump, jump!
 You're ready for ♪

10:37.380 --> 10:39.330
♪ We've flown away ♪

10:39.330 --> 10:41.330
Do any of you know
who that woman is?

10:45.330 --> 10:47.500
Let me put it another way.

10:47.500 --> 10:50.580
Do any of you who wish to graduate
with the rest of your class

10:50.580 --> 10:52.750
know who that woman is?

10:54.670 --> 10:57.380
Yeah... I know who she is.

11:03.920 --> 11:06.500
So, do you wanna
change first or should I?

11:06.500 --> 11:08.330
What do you mean, change?

11:08.330 --> 11:10.330
Into our picture day clothes?

11:10.330 --> 11:11.420
These are
our picture day clothes.

11:11.420 --> 11:15.040
(laughs) No. I have a cobalt
blue Italian linen shirt

11:15.040 --> 11:18.880
and a satin batwing bowtie from the
Diamonds Are Forever James Bond collection

11:18.880 --> 11:21.170
in a garment bag
in the teachers' lounge.

11:21.170 --> 11:23.420
Save my place.
I'll be right back.

11:23.420 --> 11:25.500
-Cyrus.
-Buffy?

11:25.500 --> 11:28.080
The whole point of this protest
is to show that we're not free

11:28.080 --> 11:29.460
to wear
what we want.

11:29.460 --> 11:31.750
But it's picture day.
Please.

11:31.750 --> 11:33.920
The James Bond
collection?

11:35.380 --> 11:37.000
(mutters)
Nobody has to know.

11:37.000 --> 11:39.500
Cyrus, we're the leaders
of this movement.

11:39.500 --> 11:41.040
We have to be strong.

11:41.040 --> 11:43.330
But I'm not strong.
I'm weak!

11:44.500 --> 11:46.380
This line is moving so fast.

11:46.380 --> 11:48.330
It'll be fine!

11:48.330 --> 11:50.210
You'll be a hero!

11:50.210 --> 11:53.460
Not to my parents, who need
this picture for their mantles

11:53.460 --> 11:56.620
to reassure themselves that they didn't
damage me in their bitter divorce.

11:56.620 --> 11:59.290
♪ ♪

12:03.460 --> 12:08.080
♪ It started
 like some stupid fairy tale ♪

12:08.080 --> 12:10.710
♪ One look
 you threw me off my feet ♪

12:12.380 --> 12:17.120
♪ And whoa, oh whoa!
 Got nowhere to run ♪

12:17.120 --> 12:21.960
♪ I'm feelin' like a fool
 I can't return ♪

12:21.960 --> 12:24.420
♪ This story welcomes
 you and I ♪

12:24.420 --> 12:26.290
♪ Whoa-oh-oh-oh! ♪

12:26.290 --> 12:28.420
♪ This time I'm up
 at the plate ♪

12:28.420 --> 12:30.580
♪ This time I'm out ♪

12:30.580 --> 12:33.250
Hey, buddy,
it's picture day.

12:33.250 --> 12:34.710
This... look on your face.

12:35.790 --> 12:37.420
Got anything else?

12:40.420 --> 12:43.670
Cyrus! I know what
your picture face should be!

12:43.670 --> 12:45.380
What?

12:45.380 --> 12:46.880
Troublemaker.

12:47.920 --> 12:49.830
I'm gonna wear it backwards.

12:49.830 --> 12:52.120
'Cause that's
what troublemakers do.

12:54.790 --> 12:56.540
♪ ♪

12:56.540 --> 12:58.620
♪ The party's here
 don't you know ♪

12:58.620 --> 13:01.040
♪ Landing like a tornado ♪

