Where's your jersey?

13:37.380 --> 13:39.290
In my locker.

13:39.290 --> 13:40.420
You have to wear it.

13:40.420 --> 13:42.330
Go get it.

13:42.330 --> 13:44.330
No, I'm good.

13:44.330 --> 13:48.460
Listen, I've got other teams
to photograph. Real ones.

13:50.540 --> 13:52.080
I hate it
when they say that.

13:52.080 --> 13:53.380
I know you do.

13:53.380 --> 13:54.790
We are a real team.

13:54.790 --> 13:56.380
We play a real sport.

13:57.500 --> 13:58.750
This is why I need you
to wear your jersey

13:58.750 --> 14:00.250
so they take us seriously.

14:00.250 --> 14:02.210
It's important.

14:02.210 --> 14:06.960
To you. Wearing this
is important to me.

14:06.960 --> 14:11.330
I'm just asking you to wear the Space
Otters jersey for five seconds.

14:11.330 --> 14:13.620
Please.
For me?

14:13.620 --> 14:15.210
-Okay.
-Yes!

14:15.210 --> 14:18.210
I'll wear the Space Otters
jersey for the picture

14:18.210 --> 14:20.880
if you can tell me why I'm
wearing a prison uniform.

14:22.960 --> 14:25.080
We talked about it earlier.

14:28.420 --> 14:31.000
I explained
why it was important to me.

14:33.580 --> 14:37.000
Yeah...
that's what I thought.

14:59.170 --> 15:00.420
Are you okay?

15:00.420 --> 15:04.330
No, I'm not okay. We did the
protests, nothing changed,

15:04.330 --> 15:08.460
and now we've both been called
to the principal's office.

15:08.460 --> 15:09.500
This is bad!

15:09.500 --> 15:11.330
What's the worst
that could happen?

15:11.330 --> 15:13.830
I could get suspended.

15:13.830 --> 15:15.790
That goes
on my permanent record!

15:17.790 --> 15:20.040
-Forever!
-Little secret.

15:21.120 --> 15:22.620
There is no permanent record.

15:22.620 --> 15:24.120
What?

15:24.120 --> 15:26.540
Yep. They made it up
to scare kids.

15:26.540 --> 15:28.330
Well, it worked.

15:28.330 --> 15:31.290
There's also no boogyman and your
face will not stay that way.

15:31.290 --> 15:32.880
I'm glad you could make it.

15:32.880 --> 15:34.750
I don't know
if you remember me.

15:36.250 --> 15:38.420
We met in the parking lot.

15:38.420 --> 15:40.210
I'm the new principal,
Dr. Metcalf.

15:40.210 --> 15:44.000
And I... (laughs) have been looking
through your permanent record.

15:46.540 --> 15:49.000
-May I see it?
-No.

15:49.000 --> 15:51.460
And yours...
had been empty.

15:51.460 --> 15:53.710
Until today.

15:53.710 --> 15:57.290
Aw, it's like my permanent
record had a baby.

16:01.040 --> 16:02.670
Dr. Metcalf,

16:02.670 --> 16:04.960
I just wanna be able
to wear my clothes.

16:04.960 --> 16:07.580
The same clothes
I wear every day.

16:07.580 --> 16:11.750
And my fellow students
have still, somehow,

16:11.750 --> 16:13.880
been able
to get an education.

16:13.880 --> 16:15.170
And I just wanna be a principal

16:15.170 --> 16:17.540
who has the respect
of his students.

16:17.540 --> 16:20.670
It's only day two
and clearly, I don't.

16:20.670 --> 16:22.670
I do respect you.

16:22.670 --> 16:25.920
But I would
respect you a lot more

16:25.920 --> 16:29.210
if we could maybe talk about
adjusting the dress code?

16:30.920 --> 16:34.790
I could... maybe talk about
adjusting the dress code

16:34.790 --> 16:36.750
if...

16:36.750 --> 16:40.710
you and your friends agree to never
wear prison uniforms again, and you...

16:40.710 --> 16:42.830
agree never
to pass them out again.

16:42.830 --> 16:45.120
Andi?

16:45.120 --> 16:46.880
I can live
with those terms.

16:46.880 --> 16:48.420
So can I.

16:48.420 --> 16:50.750
Shall we shake on it?

16:50.750 --> 16:54.290
Is... that right?
Is that how you end a protest?

16:54.290 --> 16:57.170
I don't know, this is
the first time I've ever won.

16:59.580 --> 17:01.960
You're the kind of kid that
made me want to be a principal.

17:03.500 --> 17:06.420
Ha-ha! I knew it!
It's all Sudoku!

17:06.420 --> 17:09.380
(chuckling)
In your face!

17:09.380 --> 17:11.829
And you're the kind of kid that made
me want to be a dentist. Get out.

17:11.829 --> 17:13.920
-Okay.
-Go, go, go, go, go...

17:17.420 --> 17:19.079
What should we toast?

17:19.079 --> 17:20.500
Troublemaking.

17:20.500 --> 17:22.380
All:
To troublemaking!

17:24.500 --> 17:27.579
I love today!
All these great things happened,

17:27.579 --> 17:30.120
and we're all sitting here,
and we're all happy.

17:30.120 --> 17:32.500
I mean, how many days like
that do you get in a lifetime?

17:32.500 --> 17:36.290
Not many, I can tell you, from
reading my parents' patient files.

17:36.290 --> 17:38.080
Oh, hey, more good news!

17:38.080 --> 17:39.500
-Tell me, tell me!
-The school's bringing back

17:39.500 --> 17:42.080
the photographer tomorrow
to redo picture day.

17:42.080 --> 17:45.120
You'll get to wear your James
Bond bowtie after all.

17:45.120 --> 17:47.460
But what about the
pictures they took today?

17:47.460 --> 17:50.290
-They're scrapping those.
-No, they can't!

17:50.290 --> 17:52.790
My facial choices
were on fire!

17:53.830 --> 17:56.120
I could take some pictures now,
get them printed,

17:56.120 --> 17:58.620
and you could have your eight-by-tens
by the end of the week.

18:00.080 --> 18:02.210
And I'm gonna need
some wallet-sized.

18:04.330 --> 18:06.420
(tapping on window)

18:09.790 --> 18:12.250
I bet he wants
to apologize.

18:13.540 --> 18:15.420
Then I guess
I should let him.

18:23.460 --> 18:24.920
Hey!

18:24.920 --> 18:26.540
Could we walk a little?

18:28.040 --> 18:29.250
Please.

18:30.380 --> 18:32.540
I wanted to say
congratulations.

18:32.540 --> 18:34.620
I heard they're
changing the dress code.

18:34.620 --> 18:38.000
Thanks. It feels really
good to do something.

18:38.000 --> 18:42.380
Except, now I have to get rid
of 40 prison uniforms.

18:42.380 --> 18:45.000
I feel really bad
I wasn't a part of it.

18:45.000 --> 18:49.000
I was only thinking
about Frisbee. As usual.

18:49.000 --> 18:51.670
That's okay.
We had plenty of people.

18:52.710 --> 18:53.960
I don't know if you heard,

18:53.960 --> 18:56.500
but the photographers
are comin' back tomorrow.

18:56.500 --> 18:57.960
I heard.

18:57.960 --> 19:01.040
They're going to retake the team
picture, and I want you to be there.

19:01.040 --> 19:03.250
And you can wear
whatever you want.

19:03.250 --> 19:05.420
Thanks, that's really nice.

19:06.750 --> 19:10.380
But... I don't wanna
be in the picture.

19:12.000 --> 19:13.580
So you're still mad at me.

19:13.580 --> 19:17.460
No. I'm not mad at you,
I swear.

19:17.460 --> 19:19.290
I don't wanna
be in the picture...

19:20.670 --> 19:22.710
because I don't
wanna be on the team.

19:23.790 --> 19:28.170
Stop. You can't
quit the team.

19:28.170 --> 19:30.500
Yeah, I'm pretty sure I can.

19:30.500 --> 19:31.960
You're Andiman.

19:31.960 --> 19:33.830
You love Frisbee!

19:33.830 --> 19:37.790
No... you love Frisbee.

19:37.790 --> 19:40.170
I like it.

19:40.170 --> 19:42.670
But, really, the only reason
why I joined the team

19:42.670 --> 19:45.750
was because you asked me to.

19:45.750 --> 19:47.460
Well, then I'm asking you
not to quit.

19:49.290 --> 19:50.380
See, that's the thing.

19:50.380 --> 19:52.500
You think I'll do
whatever you want,

19:52.500 --> 19:56.000
which makes perfect sense
because that is what I do.

19:57.080 --> 19:58.710
No, it isn't!

19:58.710 --> 20:01.620
Yes, it is,
think about it.

20:01.620 --> 20:05.830
I joined the team, I helped you get a
birthday present for your girlfriend,

20:05.830 --> 20:11.750
who is never nice to me. I made you
a bracelet, that you gave her.

20:11.750 --> 20:13.330
I'm sorry about that.

20:13.330 --> 20:16.290
It's fine.
I don't care about Amber.

20:16.290 --> 20:18.500
I-- I don't care
about the bracelet.

20:19.580 --> 20:21.540
I don't care
about any of it.

20:22.920 --> 20:27.500
I just want you to stop asking
me to do things for you.

20:27.500 --> 20:29.420
I will.

20:29.420 --> 20:30.290
I'm sorry.

20:30.290 --> 20:33.170
Stop apologizing,
you didn't do anything wrong.

20:33.170 --> 20:34.420
I did!

20:35.460 --> 20:37.960
I never stood up
for myself until today.

20:39.210 --> 20:43.380
But I want to again tomorrow,
and the day after that.

20:45.540 --> 20:49.120
But being around you
makes it really hard.

20:49.120 --> 20:51.710
What are you saying?

20:51.710 --> 20:54.080
We're still friends, right?

20:55.460 --> 20:57.670
Jonah, be honest...

20:59.880 --> 21:01.540
were we ever?

21:19.420 --> 21:20.580
Jonah:
 Next, on Andi Mack...

21:20.580 --> 21:24.290
A Jonah-free lifestyle
is way less complicated.

21:24.290 --> 21:25.540
Do you know what's going on
with Andi?

21:25.540 --> 21:29.080
I wouldn't call it mad,
more coolly detached.

21:29.080 --> 21:30.380
You like her, don't you?

21:30.380 --> 21:31.880
I gotta go.

21:31.880 --> 21:34.290
Buffy:
 If we race, and I beat you,

21:34.290 --> 21:35.830
will you still talk to me?

21:35.830 --> 21:38.790
If I beat you, will you still
talk to me?

21:38.790 --> 21:41.170
You're breaking up with me?

21:41.170 --> 21:42.460
How dare you!

21:42.460 --> 21:43.500
You're in middle school,

21:43.500 --> 21:46.380
do you know how lucky you are
to be dating me?

